4 Use InferCNV to obtain a CNV heatmap and the CNV score

Note: For the inferCNV package, we refer to https://github.com/broadinstitute/inferCNV.

4.1 Run infercnv

Note: The following infercnv::run program will take up large memory and much time (almost 1 day for the following code). Youd better apply for a node with large memory (I suggest 100GB memory) to run the program. Also, the default output will take up large disk space. Here we need to prepare a gene sequence file, download it from the following: https://support.10xgenomics.com/single-cell-gene-expression/software/downloads/latest

library(infercnv)

celltype <- "endocrine"

PCids <- c("S7","S13","S14","S15","S17","S22","S23","S24","S6","S9","S11","S12","S10","S25") 
datapath <- "./Data/PCsamples"

i <- 1

commongenes <- list()
for (PCid in PCids){
  PCobj <- readRDS(file.path(datapath,PCid,paste0(PCid,"_clustered_dim20_res0_3.rds")))
  print(dim(PCobj@assays$RNA@counts))
  commongenes[[i]] <- rownames(PCobj)
  i <- i+1
}
commongenes <- Reduce(intersect,commongenes)
commongenes <- intersect(commongenes,rownames(NF))

##### build "raw_counts_matrix"
PC_rawcounts <- c()
for (PCid in PCids){
  PCobj <- readRDS(file.path(datapath,PCid,paste0(PCid,"_clustered_dim20_res0_3.rds")))
  print(PCid)
  load(file.path(datapath,PCid,paste0(PCid,"_cluster_dim20_res0_3_indiv_cell_label.rdata")))
  sc_indiv_cell_label <- as.character(sc_indiv_cell_label)
  if (celltype=="endocrine") sc_indiv_cell_label[sc_indiv_cell_label=="endocrine(beta)"] = celltype
  if (sum(sc_indiv_cell_label == celltype)){
    PC_rawcounts <- cbind(PC_rawcounts,PCobj@assays$RNA@counts[commongenes,sc_indiv_cell_label == celltype])
  }
}

NF_rawcounts <- NF_raw@assays$RNA@counts[commongenes,]
raw_counts_matrix <- cbind(PC_rawcounts,NF_rawcounts)

## build "annotations_file"
PC_annotations <- rep(paste0(celltype,"_PC"),ncol(PC_rawcounts))
NF_annotations <- rep(paste0(celltype),ncol(NF_rawcounts))
annotations_file <- as.data.frame(c(as.character(PC_annotations),as.character(NF_annotations)))
colnames(PC_rawcounts) <- make.names(colnames(PC_rawcounts), unique=T)
rownames(annotations_file) <- c(colnames(PC_rawcounts),colnames(NF_rawcounts))

## read "gene_order_file"
gene_order_file=read.table("./Data/refdata-gex-GRCh38-2020-A/geneOrderingFile.txt",row.names=1) 

infercnv_obj = CreateInfercnvObject(raw_counts_matrix=raw_counts_matrix,
                                    annotations_file=annotations_file,
                                    delim="\t",
                                    gene_order_file=gene_order_file,
                                    ref_group_names=c(paste0(celltype,"_PC")))

rm(list=ls()[!ls() %in% c("infercnv_obj")])
gc()

# perform infercnv operations to reveal cnv signal
infercnv_obj = infercnv::run(infercnv_obj,
                             cutoff=0.1,  
                             out_dir="./Data/InferCNV_NFEndocrineVsPCEndocrine",  # dir is auto-created for storing outputs
                             cluster_by_groups=T,   
                             denoise=T,
                             HMM=T,
                             output_format="pdf"
                             )

4.2 Compute CNV score

Note: You may refer to https://github.com/broadinstitute/infercnv/issues/393 for the discussion on how to compute CNV score. We can get the modified gene expression values infercnv.references.txt for reference cells and infercnv.observations.txt for observation cells in the output. To obtain the CNV score for each cell, we adopted a method different than that in the discussion: \[ \text{CNV score}_{\text{cell }i} = \sum_j | \text{Gene expression}_{\text{cell } i,j} - 1 |. \]

obs = read.table("./Data/cnv/infercnv.observations.txt")
refs = read.table("./Data/cnv/infercnv.references.txt")

obs <- obs-1
refs <- refs-1
score_obs <- colSums(abs(obs))
names(score_obs) <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(names(score_obs),'\\.'),function(x) Reduce(function(y,z) paste(y,z,sep='-'),x)))
score_refs =  colSums(abs(refs))

5.5 Figure 2I: gene signatures enrichmented analysis from MLP signature genes.

5.5.1 Find Differentially Expressed Genes.

unique(NF_endoc $state)
subset <- NF_endoc [,NF_endoc $state== "AGR2_high" ]

group1 <- sapply(unique(subset$orig.ident),function(patient){if (sum(subset$orig.ident==patient)) rowSums(subset@assays$RNA@counts[,subset$orig.ident==patient,drop=F]) else rep(0,nrow(subset))})

subset <- NF_endoc [,NF_endoc  $state== "AGR2_low" ]
group2 <- sapply(unique(subset$orig.ident),function(patient){if (sum(subset$orig.ident==patient)) rowSums(subset@assays$RNA@counts[,subset$orig.ident==patient,drop=F]) else rep(0,nrow(subset))})

colnames(group1) <- paste0("treated",seq_len(ncol(group1)))
colnames(group2) <- paste0("untreated",seq_len(ncol(group2)))

cts <- as.matrix(cbind(group1,group2))
coldata <- data.frame(condition=c(rep("treated",ncol(group1)),rep("untreated",ncol(group2))))
rownames(coldata) <- colnames(cts)

cts <- cts[rowSums(cts)>0,]
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = cts+1,
                              colData = coldata,
                              design = ~ condition)
keep <- rowSums(counts(dds)) >= 10
dds <- dds[keep,]
dds$condition <- factor(dds$condition, levels = c("treated","untreated"))
dds <- DESeq(dds)
res <- results(dds)
res <- as.data.frame(res)

##### compute the expression ratio for each gene and each cluster 
group1 <- NF_endoc @assays$RNA@counts[rownames(res),NF_endoc  $state== "AGR2_high" ]
group2 <- NF_endoc @assays$RNA@counts[rownames(res),NF_endoc  $state== "AGR2_low" ]

res <- cbind(res,group1prop=rowSums(group1>0)/ncol(group1),group2prop=rowSums(group2>0)/ncol(group2))

write.csv(res,file=paste0("./Figure2/PseudoBulkDEGs_AGR2_high_vs_AGR2_low.csv"))
